Meet the Team
Betsy Cleveland
,
,
President & CEO
Betsy brings a wealth of experience with her to the chamber, having served as the Executive Director of the Haines City Area Chamber of Commerce (now the Northeast Polk Chamber), the Director of Community Services for the Polk County Supervisor of Elections, a Community Liaison Director for the Polk County Public Schools, and as a District Legislative Aide for State Senator JD Alexander.
Connect with Betsy on LinkedIn
.
Brianna Price
,
VP of Operations, Communications & Programs
Brianna Price moved from Columbus, Ohio to Winter Haven in 2005 and is currently living in Auburndale with her husband, baby and fur-baby. Brianna spent two years studying at Polk State College and received her Bachelors degree in Communications at Southeastern University in Lakeland. Brianna champions our communications and marketing efforts, as well as programs like Endeavor Serves, Morning Momentum and more. When she's not working on communications for the Chamber, she enjoys exploring the North Georgia mountains with her husband and little one. You can often find her snuggled up with her dog and spending time with family and friends.
Connect with Bri on LinkedIn
.
Inga Stettler
, Finance & Facilities Manager
Inga moved from Michigan to Winter Haven at the age of four and has lived in the area ever since, other than attending college at University of South Florida.  Prior to becoming the Business Manager at the Chamber, Inga was the Budgetary Accountant with the Polk Education Foundation, a direct support organization of the Polk County School Board. Inga is married with two adult children. In her free time, she enjoys spending time with friends and spending time at the beach.
Connect with Inga on LinkedIn.
Lynn Polston, Membership Development & Services Manager
Lynn has been involved in the Chamber since 2017, became an ambassador in 2018 and has fallen in love with the Winter Haven Community.
Connect with Lynn on LinkedIn
.
​
Stephanie Selz, Programs & Membership Administrative Assistant
Stephanie is a Lakeland native, having lived in the area since 2004.  Stephanie graduated from Florida Gulf Coast University with
a Bachelor of Arts in Sociology and a minor in Psychology.  Outside of her professional endeavors, Stephanie enjoys playing volleyball, attending concerts, and spending time at the beach.
Connect with Steph on LinkedIn
.

Leadership Winter Haven
Leadership Winter Haven
Leadership Winter Haven was founded in 1980. Since that time the program has been dedicated to developing a well informed and diverse pool of leadership talent ready to help the community and area reach its full potential.  In the course of the program, participants leadership skills are nurtured while they are exposed to the spectrum of business, industry, governmental and social issues that confront Winter Haven’s current leaders and will challenge the leaders of tomorrow.
Since the program’s inception as one of Florida’s earliest community leadership programs (and Polk County’s first), over 500 people have completed the course. Leadership Winter Haven alumni represent a strong communications network within Greater Winter Haven uniting people of varied interests and backgrounds. From agribusiness to entrepreneur, finance to public servant, the program is rich with diversity.
LWH graduates possess a unique understanding of the complexity of our region. Participants learn first hand the assets, opportunities, challenges and needs within our community, county and Central Florida.
Graduates of Leadership Winter Haven are found throughout not only business, government and community organizations but serving as effective, aware volunteer leaders on Boards of civic organizations and community projects. The benefit of this leadership program is the shaping of a vibrant yet diverse group of individuals who, through well informed decisions, will help our community face tomorrow’s challenges.
Application
You might be wondering about the application process, who should participate, how individuals are selected and what you stand to gain from this experience. If so, check out our
application
below
for more details. The application will give you all the information you will need to learn more about this program!
All applications are due by June 30, 2025.

With their support, the Chamber is able to accomplish incredible forward motion with our membership, the City of Winter Haven, our business community and beyond. We truly appreciate the time, talent and treasure that they give to the Chamber's mission and vision.
